service: An Amazon S3 table represents a structured dataset consisting of tabular data in Apache Parquet format and related metadata. This data is stored inside an S3 table as a subresource. All tables in a table bucket are stored in the Apache Iceberg table format. Through integration with the AWS Glue Data Catalog you can interact with your tables using AWS analytics services, such as Amazon Athena and Amazon Redshift. Amazon S3 manages maintenance of your tables through automatic file compaction and snapshot management. For more information, see Amazon S3 table buckets.

operations.CreateNamespace: Creates a namespace. A namespace is a logical grouping of tables within your table bucket, which you can use to organize tables. For more information, see Table namespaces.
operations.CreateTable: Creates a new table associated with the given namespace in a table bucket.
operations.GetTableBucketMaintenanceConfiguration: Gets details about a maintenance configuration for a given table bucket.
operations.GetTableBucketPolicy: Gets details about a table bucket policy.
operations.GetTableMaintenanceConfiguration: Gets details about the maintenance configuration of a table.
operations.GetTableMaintenanceJobStatus: Gets the status of a maintenance job for a table.
operations.GetTableMetadataLocation: Gets the location of the table metadata.
operations.ListNamespaces: Lists the namespaces within a table bucket.
operations.ListTables: List tables in the given table bucket.
operations.PutTableBucketMaintenanceConfiguration: Creates a new maintenance configuration or replaces an existing maintenance configuration for a table bucket.
operations.PutTableBucketPolicy: Creates a new maintenance configuration or replaces an existing table bucket policy for a table bucket.
operations.PutTableMaintenanceConfiguration: Creates a new maintenance configuration or replaces an existing maintenance configuration for a table.
operations.PutTablePolicy: Creates a new maintenance configuration or replaces an existing table policy for a table.
operations.UpdateTableMetadataLocation: Updates the metadata location for a table.
